# Step-by-Step method to store static websites in an S3 bucket.
S3 is best for storing static files. Static contents are managed by S3.

**Step 1** Search and click open S3.
![image](https://github.com/ravinder-panwar/static-website-in-s3/assets/133412857/2984834d-6403-45b0-b78c-a056a0b6778f)


**Step 2** Create a new bucket.
![image](https://github.com/ravinder-panwar/static-website-in-s3/assets/133412857/cb085ada-8bd0-411c-ab73-d2ec026f21e7)


**Step 3** Configure the name, region, and other settings according to your need.
Note: Bucket name must be in lowercase.
![image](https://github.com/ravinder-panwar/static-website-in-s3/assets/133412857/2b5e5635-ddb6-45a6-adc2-9ef46ec8cec7)
![image](https://github.com/ravinder-panwar/static-website-in-s3/assets/133412857/abb2748a-c8d8-4bc2-b697-d4059f2daf26)
![image](https://github.com/ravinder-panwar/static-website-in-s3/assets/133412857/6a30a27e-11c7-4ebe-a20f-74bd47cd8c0a)


**Step 4** Click on "Create bucket".
![image](https://github.com/ravinder-panwar/static-website-in-s3/assets/133412857/f8ab69b1-396c-4a3f-a7b8-0b94f5f9508c)


**Step 5** Write a website code and save it on the desktop. Here, I saved my code by the name "static.html".
![image](https://github.com/ravinder-panwar/static-website-in-s3/assets/133412857/3576df59-a381-4c83-aabc-9446fd98afd3)


**Step 6** Go to the S3 bucket and open the bucket that you just created.
![image](https://github.com/ravinder-panwar/static-website-in-s3/assets/133412857/388b6f7a-6e7d-4abd-bcb0-b199b04bc88f)


**Step 7**  Create an object and upload a file we created in Step 5.
![image](https://github.com/ravinder-panwar/static-website-in-s3/assets/133412857/e796933a-08e0-43d8-9577-bf870bf8f8d4)
![image](https://github.com/ravinder-panwar/static-website-in-s3/assets/133412857/9d127ea2-a7e7-499b-b9ec-ab4e0f8507a4)
![image](https://github.com/ravinder-panwar/static-website-in-s3/assets/133412857/e16afafe-b3eb-494f-8733-f5bd7bef68ce)
![image](https://github.com/ravinder-panwar/static-website-in-s3/assets/133412857/074e6e14-97d5-4f6e-8a55-2db438e4e343)


**Step 8** Select the object, go to actions, and click on "Make public using ACL".
![image](https://github.com/ravinder-panwar/static-website-in-s3/assets/133412857/4929e990-1d2b-4526-abaa-e62b471c8bb4)


**Step 9** Now again select the object, go to properties and scroll down and enable "Static web hosting".
![image](https://github.com/ravinder-panwar/static-website-in-s3/assets/133412857/13bae720-39ce-49a2-927c-6270f8d3e235)


**Step 10** Copy and paste the link on the browser to check if your static website is working or not.
![image](https://github.com/ravinder-panwar/static-website-in-s3/assets/133412857/fba853ef-c75d-4b59-919a-bc64201b65e2)


**Step 11** Done. Congrats. Our static website is successfully running.
![image](https://github.com/ravinder-panwar/static-website-in-s3/assets/133412857/06f26c10-c8c0-45dd-8810-02dc21268b5b)












